			Point of Interest
			
	*Anghal Desert : first area of this region. Is the second biggest, located in western side of it.
		*Golden Coasts : located in the eastern side of this area, biggest zone here and the place where players grind exp from monsters.
		*Black Sands : located in the western side of the area consist in a field of barren desert with many huge blocks of stones and hills.
			*Goldcap Town : this is the first human settlement where the players will arrive once they teleport to this region.Located in the south-west of this area.
			*Sundry Lake : a lake which is located right in the center of the area that create an imaginary separation between "Golden Coasts" and "Black Sands".
	*Golden Fields : second area, biggest of the region. Located in the middle and consist in barren lands.
		*Alddan Field : located in the western side of the area, biggest.
			*Ancient Ruins : located in the north side of the area and is surrounded by stone walls. Lead to "Barh Khaon Cave" a dungeon deep in the mountains.
			*Verian Stable : tavern, located in the middle of the map, right where the two territories meet.
		*Arid Savanna : located in the eastern side of the area. In this place can be found trees and savanna wild animals.
			*Southern Abyll Town : located in the southern side of the area, surrounded by ruins of a settlement and huge blocks of stones.
	*Fierdon : third area, the smallest. Located in eastern side of the region. Have access to the "Great Sea".
		*Riven Fields : located in the western side of the area, biggest. This area is severed by few rivers that come from the mountain and leads to the eastern side
and ends in the "Great Sea".
			*Stumb Stables : a small village where a few NPCs study wild animals of this territory. Located in west, very close to the mountain.
		*Greenden Savanna : located in the east side of the area, consisting in huge vegetation and tall forest.
			*Riddleport : is the human settlement in this area, located in the east side of the area as a port at the "Great Sea".